<a href='http://herbaria4.herb.berkeley.edu/eflora_display.php?tid=10429'><h3>View taxon page for Cerastium</h3></a><blockquote><h3></h3>
<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#OH1'">1.</a><a name="OH1."> </a> Annual (or appearing so); stems generally all flowering, ascending to erect

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#OH2'">2.</a><a name="OH2."> </a> Calyx 8.5&ndash;12 mm; fruit 14&ndash;22 mm; seeds 0.9&ndash;1.1 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18665">.....&nbsp;C. dichotomum</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#OH2.">2'</a><a name="OH2'"> </a> Calyx 3&ndash;7 mm; fruit 3.5&ndash;11 mm; seeds &plusmn; 0.4&ndash;1 mm

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#OH3'">3.</a><a name="OH3."> </a> Upper bracts scarious-margined; scarious margin of most outer sepals 0.2&ndash;0.6 mm wide <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=49818">.....&nbsp;C. fontanum subsp. vulgare</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#OH3.">3'</a><a name="OH3'"> </a> Upper bracts not scarious (rarely with minute scarious tip); scarious margin of most outer sepals &lt; 0.1 mm wide

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#OH4'">4.</a><a name="OH4."> </a> Flower parts 4(5); sepals with 0 hairs exceeding tip; bracts not scarious or rarely with minute scarious tip; pedicels in fruit generally > sepals <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18666">.....&nbsp;[C. diffusum]</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#OH4.">4'</a><a name="OH4'"> </a> Flower parts 5; sepals with some hairs exceeding tip by 0.2&ndash;0.8 mm; bracts not scarious; pedicels in fruit (except lowest) &lt; sepals <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18675">.....&nbsp;C. glomeratum</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 0 ;"><a href="#OH1.">1'</a><a name="OH1'"> </a> Perennial herb; stems both non-flowering (mat-forming) and flowering (&plusmn; erect)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#OH5'">5.</a><a name="OH5."> </a> Petals 1.5 mm &lt; to 0.5 mm > sepals <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=49818">.....&nbsp;C. fontanum subsp. vulgare</a> (2)

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 7 ;"><a href="#OH5.">5'</a><a name="OH5'"> </a> Petals &plusmn; 1.2&ndash;6 mm > sepals

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#OH6'">6.</a><a name="OH6."> </a> Leaves not clustered in flower stem axils; petals 1.2&ndash;2.8 mm > sepals; fruit 5.5&ndash;8.5 mm; seeds 0.7&ndash;0.8 mm; 2900&ndash;4300 m <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18654">.....&nbsp;C. beeringianum</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 14 ;"><a href="#OH6.">6'</a><a name="OH6'"> </a> Leaves clustered in flower stem axils, especially below; petals 3&ndash;6 mm > sepals; fruit (7.5) 9&ndash;16 mm; seeds &plusmn; 1&ndash;1.5 mm; &lt; 2500 m

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#OH7'">7.</a><a name="OH7."> </a> Stems 5&ndash;20(30) cm; petals 7.5&ndash;9 mm; sepals 4.2&ndash;6(7) mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=49810">.....&nbsp;C. arvense subsp. strictum</a>

<P class="keyText" style="padding-left : 21 ;"><a href="#OH7.">7'</a><a name="OH7'"> </a> Stems 15&ndash;45 cm; petals 10&ndash;15 mm; sepals 6&ndash;9 mm <a href="/cgi-bin/get_IJM.pl?tid=18630">.....&nbsp;C. viride</a></blockquote><P>
